object.at: Repositories are listed in the same order as they appear in the Campaign Properties.
The FTP server name may be a hostname or an IP address. When using an IPv6 address surround it with "[" and "]".
The username to login as on the FTP server.
The password associated with the above username. It will not display here nor will it be saved for future use.
Set this to one of the repositories in the list above. You may double-click an entry from the list, use keyboard cut/paste, or type in the text.
Double-click a repository to copy the repository location into the Save To: field.
These repositories are from the Campaign Properties on the Edit menu.
If your FTP login requires that you change directory to navigate to the location of the repository's index.gz directory, enter the directory name here.
Place a checkmark in each repository that you want to search for existing assets.
This is the index.gz that will be updated with the new image information.

Some FTP servers may not allow MapTool to create a directory. If this is the case for your server yet you want new assets in their own directory, uncheck this field and create the directory yourself, then specify that directory as the location on the server.
